Aparna Sagaram is a licensed marriage and family therapist practicing in Philadelphia, PA. She identifies as a second generation South Asian woman. She specializes in working with children of immigrants, immigrant family dynamics, and BIPOC folks. She also specializes in working with couples navigate relationship issues related to identity, inner child, and culture through an anti racism lens.

I am a Psychiatric Mental Health Nurse Practitioner offering therapy and/or psychiatric medication prescribing for adults ages 18+. I offer a warm, empathic, non-judgmental, and collaborative treatment approach. I was born in China and moved to the US when I was 6 and am interested in giving back to the Asian-American community. Having a shared cultural background and experience with a provider can be incredibly helpful. If you're interested in becoming a new client, please contact the schedulers at 267-358-6155 ext 1 and mention my name. My website has more info including costs.

Hello! I am a Board Certified Art Therapist, Licensed Professional Counselor and Board Certified Transgender Care Therapist. I work with adolescents and adults and approach therapy from an experiential, feminist, multicultural approach. I utilize art making and expressive therapies to help facilitate greater self-acceptance, self-confidence, personal growth, and to empower you to create positive change. I specialize in working with the LGBTQIA2s+ communities, and individuals with diverse multicultural and ethnic backgrounds. I am a listener and am here to hear your story and provide wholehearted counseling to support you and your journey.
therapists.what_insurance_accepted: United, Optum, Aetna, Highmark, Cigna, UPMC

therapists.additional_information:
Bri is a warm, empathetic, and non-judgmental Licensed Professional Counselor who strives to create a safe place for each and every client to feel comfortable sharing their story.

Working from a relational, client centered approach, Bri believes in the importance of developing a strong, authentic therapeutic relationship. She tailors interventions to each individual to help them understand the relationship between their physical body, thoughts, and feelings. 

Bri also practices from a trauma informed, social justice lens and is passionate about working with all individuals who possess any marginalized identity.
therapists.what_insurance_accepted: I’m paneled with nearly all major insurance plans 😊

therapists.additional_information:
Catherine Mok, LMSW is a therapist at Austin Family Counseling. She specializes in working with children, adolescents, parents, individuals and families using a collaborative and client-centered approach tailored to the unique needs of each client.  She uses a variety of therapeutic methods including Play Therapy, Sandtray Therapy, Attachment theory, Cognitive Behavioral Therapy, Family Systems Therapy, and Strength-based Therapy. 
She is also a Certified Positive Discipline Parent Educator and enjoys working with parents    and families. Her goal is to help her clients discover their strengths and empower them to reach their full potential.

I am a licensed psychologist and licensed specialist in school psychology (LSSP) in Austin, Texas. I specialize in working with anxiety, perfectionism, high achievers, racial trauma, and children of immigrants. I practice from a systems-informed framework incorporating anti-oppressive and liberation psychological practices. My approach to therapy is integrative and person-centered. I use a relational approach to help you understand how your past affects your present and where you learned the habits and beliefs you carry with you so you can make intentional choices for your future aligned with your values.

Therapy is all about finding the right fit.  It may help you to know that I am a child of immigrants, am a wife and mother, this is not my first career, and that I lost a parent to cancer.  I do not share these things to equate it to your life experiences but rather to inform you that I, too, am human.  We all age.  We try to understand and make sense of who we are and our purpose in this world.  We experience loss.  I can not guarantee you change, but I can guarantee you that I will be human with you.

Hello! I'm so glad you stopped by. A little background on me:

I received my BA in Psychology and English from The University of Texas at Austin.
Having a lifelong interest in the stories people carry, I sought to pursue a Masters in Counseling from Reformed Theological Seminary in order to help people understand their past so they may be meaningfully engaged in their present. 
EMDR Certified

Welcome! I am glad you have reached out for support. Having counseled since 2003, I specialize in working with women who are struggling with anxiety, depression, abuse, trauma, codependency, relationships (dating, marriage and parenting), boundaries, grief and loss, faith, and other adjustments in life.
I provide evidence based counseling modalities such as Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) and Psychodynamic Therapy. I also use EMDR (Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing) for trauma as well as Neurofeedback to decrease symptoms of anxiety and depression. Therapeutic modality used is based on the comfort of the client.

Dr. Jenny Wang is a Taiwanese American, clinical psychologist, speaker, and mental health activist who works from a social justice and trauma-informed framework. She is the founder of the @asiansformentalhealth community on Instagram and is passionate about destigmatizing mental health for Asians. Her clinical and professional interests focus on Asian American identity, mental health advocacy and racial trauma. She created the Asians for Mental Health directory in order to help Asian Americans find culturally reverent mental health care.

Joy Chen is a LPC Associate supervised by Audrey Omenson, LPC-S. She is a former English Language Arts teacher. Joy obtained her master’s degree in marriage and family therapy from Fuller Theological Seminary. Joy has worked in community mental health centers treating depression, anxiety, trauma, loss and grief, and adjustment issues. Joy works with individuals ages 6 and older, holding special interest in working with young adults experiencing intergenerational conflict and racial trauma. She draws from a variety of therapeutic approaches and theories, including psychodynamic, person-centered, family systems, and attachment.

I work with children (6+), teens, adults, and older adults. My area of specialty for the last 10 years has been grief/loss. I also have extensive experience working with foster care/adoption, chronic and terminal illness, aging, caregiving, trauma, ADHD, and anxiety. I am passionate about equipping the family unit through parent coaching as well as family therapy. I am EMDR trained and use a wide variety of different therapeutic modalities. 

My hope is that you feel known, valued, and safe. It is my great privilege to meet you wherever you are and to walk alongside you as we seek truth, clarity, and restoration together. You are not alone.

As a therapist, I strive to create a safe space for my clients to explore and evolve. I’m passionate about working with clients struggling with trauma, men specific counseling, attachment and anxiety, depression, LGBTQ and identity work. I use a variety of skills, including eye movement desensitization and reprocessing (EMDR), cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT), and solution-focused therapy to facilitate each client’s therapeutic process. ​

I believe my clients know themselves better than anyone else, and that self-awareness and acceptance is necessary for growth to occur. I advocate for my clients to see their own influence for change.
therapists.what_insurance_accepted: United Healthcare/UMR, Cigna, Select Health, EMI, Blue Cross Blue Shield, Pehp,

therapists.additional_information: I provide therapy in a school-based setting in Utah. I have a closed client load at this time. Most of my experience has been focused on working with domestic violence victims, children and adolescents and schools.

I am a licensed clinical psychologist in Virginia working primarily with clients in VA, D.C., and MD. Through PSYPACT, I can provide teletherapy to clients in 17+ states. Before opening my own practice, I worked with individuals and couples at a group practice, and before that at Swarthmore College’s Counseling and Psychological Services. I also have experience working with clients in outpatient and inpatient hospitals, community mental health clinics, and a private school. Through a culturally responsive approach and trauma informed and social justice lens, I help clients build a sense of hope through acceptance, compassion, and empowerment.

I am a 1.5 generation Chinese American board certified psychologist who specializes in cultural identity, relationships, Asian American mental health, and emotionally focused therapy. I conduct individual and couples therapy. I also conduct psychological testing for a range of issues, including ADHD, learning disabilities, overall mental health, and personality exploration. My passion is working with people of color to increase insight and connection, process and heal past wounds, and identify values for future goals.
therapists.what_insurance_accepted: Premera, Lyra, First Choice Health Network, Kaiser Permanente PPO

therapists.additional_information: I’m a therapist specializing in Asian shame, trauma, and addictions, especially when it comes to porn/sex.

I strive, first and foremost, to provide for my clients a brave space to explore, question, learn, practice, fail, and try again.  I am also eager to help clients learn and internalize skills that will help them achieve their goals.  My therapeutic approach uses both a solution-focused and cognitive-behavioral therapy lens.  I also incorporate art & play therapy, as well as bibliotherapy.

Diane is a trauma informed psychotherapist and she is fully trained in EMDR through EMDRIA. Diane is experienced in working with older teens, college students and adults struggling with sexual trauma, behavioral addictions, anxiety, depression and intergenerational trauma. She is Korean-American, her parents immigrated from South Korea and able to empathize with various struggles that immigrant families experience. Diane speaks fluent Korean and English and able to offer bi-lingual, and multicultural counseling services.

As an Asian American therapist, I am passionate about the intersections of mental health, faith, and race. Your cultural upbringing, ethnically or religiously has shaped you, both in life-giving and painful ways. I see your struggle of sitting in that tension. I see your exhaustion from fighting the negative voices that constantly pervade your thoughts. I see the effort you’ve made to keep going despite the immense weight of pain you feel. You were not designed to do life alone. I believe in your inherent worth regardless of life circumstances. You yearn for freedom and release from limiting beliefs.

Harry Dixon, MA, LMHC, LPCC is a gay Korean American cis male licensed professional clinical counselor providing individual counseling in San Diego, CA as well as Seattle, WA.  He is unique among counselors in his ability to understand issues resulting from cultural and intergenerational conflicts as well as concerns and struggles around intersectional identities. He can help you navigate through these identities and help you discover the true you so that you may have a fuller and more exciting life experience.

Dr. Chong is a clinical health psychologist interested in interdisciplinary care. She completed a postdoctoral fellowship at Stanford University School of Medicine and received her Ph.D. in clinical psychology from UT Southwestern. Dr. Chong promotes the use of a biopsychosocial approach to help individuals living with chronic health conditions improve their functioning and quality of life.

I strive to provide an empathetic and inviting environment, keeping in mind the stigma and challenges of mental health in all cultures and communities, especially within the AAPI community. I am a Licensed Independent Clinical Social Worker and approach services with a holistic and collaborative approach utilizing solutions-based and trauma-informed practices to best tailor support for each individual. I incorporate modalities in my treatments such as EMDR, DBT, and CBT.
therapists.what_insurance_accepted: Community Health Plan of Washington, Molina, Regence, Premera

therapists.additional_information: I believe in the power of therapy because I have experienced freedom, hope, and joy in my own therapeutic journey. My goal is to partner with you to empower you in your own journey. My experience as an immigrant to the United States and working with refugees from around the world, drives my love of working with people from all cultures. I am a Korean American woman, and I look forward to meeting clients as they are, in their own unique beauty. I offer teletherapy to Washington State residents, specializing in childhood traumas, immigrant/People of Color experience, and women's issues. I utilize long-term, relational, trauma-focused therapy.

I'm a licensed mental health counselor and state-certified geriatric mental health specialist.  Post-graduate clinical experience since 2004 mostly in social service settings and a few years of private practice.  I currently primarily work with members of marginalized communities including BIPOC people mainly Asians, immigrants, LGBTQ+ people, people with chronic medical conditions, aging adults and/or those who are neurodivergent.  With my expansive background working in social services and serving helpers, I enjoy working with caregivers and people who work is healthcare/social service settings too.
therapists.what_insurance_accepted: Aetna, First Choice, Kaiser PPO (and HMO/CORE with prior authorization), Lifewise of WA, Lyra EAP, Premera Blue Cross, most out of state Blue Cross Blue Shield plans (need to verify)

therapists.additional_information: Ivy is a second-generation Asian American Licensed Marriage & Family Therapist, Life & Relationship Coach, Speaker, and Author who offers trauma-informed and social justice-minded therapy and coaching for individuals with a holistic, intuitive, and collaborative approach. She has been supporting her clients for 16+ years and her specialties include: First & Second-Generation Asian American Mental Health, Ancestral & Intergenerational Trauma Healing, Healing Codependency, Relationships, Self-Love, Self-Esteem, Self-Confidence, & Self-Worth, and Reconnecting to Your Body, Your Emotions, Your Wisdom, Your Intuition, & Your Truth.
